Description: Visualize the process from user registration to the first booking and also depict major errors in the system.
KPI measures the average time from user registration to their first reservation. In other words, it reflects how quickly users engage with our system.
KPI pertains to the average number of reservations made by a single user in the system. This allows us to understand how often our users utilize our booking services.
KPI presents the average value of service fees, providing insight into the average amount users spend on a single reservation or service.

KPI displays the total number of reservations made and performs a percentage comparison with the results from the previous year. This enables us to assess the growth or decline dynamics of our business compared to previous periods.
